cs.IT, cs.CR, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.MM

The paper deals with the design of secure wireless transmissions, which involves information theory (cs.IT), cryptography (cs.CR), networking (cs.NI), control systems (cs.SY), and multimedia (cs.MM). The focus on waveform design and physical-layer security suggests that cs.IT and cs.CR are the most likely categories, followed by cs.NI and cs.SY for the networking and control aspects, and cs.MM for the potential applications in multimedia communications.
